snippet.textDisplay: The "AH AH AH AH" is actually a popular motif called the Dies Irae first recorded in 13th century! Musicians have been using it countless time since. Frozen does it in the style of the kulning, a traditional Scandinavian herding call.

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay hear me out
In the scene where they enter there parents boat we see that not only did Elsa bring the memory of them on the ship but if you listen you can hear her mother scream before dying which to me as a teen who never thought Disney would do that made me feel bad but after this she blames her powers and herself for causing her parents to leave I think this is why this song was such a importance cuz you see Elsa finally letting go as in she let’s go of the guilt she thinks she has to have for her parents death especially when it’s her mother you see it shows how important Elsa mother was to where it’s only her mother that tells her it’s okay it’s not your fault embrace your gift and let go of the fear and blame you put on yourself which speaks to a lot of viewers who sometimes put the need of perfection on themselves hearing this is like telling them it’s okay embrace who you are not what you think people need or want which I give Disney my ever loving respect
